{% extends "layouts/_base.njk" %}
{% set title = "Not.Bot | Verified Creator" %}
{% set menu = "products" %}
{% block content %}
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <section class="hero verified-creator-hero">
        <div class="hero-container">
            <div class="hero-content">
                <h1>not.bot Verified Creator</h1>
            </div>
            <div class="hero-illustration">
                <img src="/img/celebrity.png" alt="Name tag line art illustration" class="hero-image"/>
            </div>
            <div class="hero-subheading w-100">
                <p>Deepfakes are everywhere, and they’re getting very good.</p>
                <div class="hero-benefits">
                    <div class="benefit-column">
                        <p>How will we know what’s real?</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
    <!-- Below-the-fold Content Section -->
    <section class="content-section">
        <div
            class="content-container">
            <!-- Platypus and Explanation -->
            <div class="content-block">
                <div class="content-image">
                    <img src="/img/angry-puppet.png" alt="Platypus line art illustration"/>
                </div>
                <div class="content-text">
                    <p>
                        <strong>For influencers</strong>, deepfakes mean lost revenue, as unscrupulous marketers bypass the influencer and
                            produce their own product placements and promotions using that influencer’s likeness.</p>
                    <p>
                        <strong>For politicians</strong>, business leaders and news agencies, deepfakes lend credibility to lies. When an
                            unethical activist “rolls the tape” to present fake evidence, everyone loses.</p>
                    <p>
                        <strong>For celebrities</strong>
                        and anyone with a public image, deepfakes can wreck reputation.  The court of public opinion can be swift and vicious.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <!-- Julia Vanity Name System Block -->
            <div class="emphasis-block verified-creator">
                <div class="emphasis-content">
                    <p>Verified Creator badges securely link a not.bot alias to a specific social media account. Any stickers created with
                        that badge will show the Verified Creator badge instead of a reserved name or petname, and will be highlighted in a
                        special color.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
    <section class="content-panel panel-light-grey">
        <div class="panel-container">
            <h2 class="panel-heading">Here's how it works</h2>
            <div
                class="how-it-works-content verified-creator">
                <!-- Add to Contacts -->
                <div class="feature-block feature-left">
                    <div class="feature-text">
                        <div class="feature-step">
                            <div class="feature-number">1</div>
                            <p>To request a Verified Creator badge for one of your aliases, you will be given a small block of text to post on your
                                social media account.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-image">
                        <img src="/img/verifier-content.png" alt="Verified Creator Request"/>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-block feature-left">
                    <div class="feature-text">
                        <div class="feature-step">
                            <div class="feature-number">2</div>
                            <p>Once it has been posted, submit a publicly-accessible URL where Julia Social can confirm it has been posted by that
                                account</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-image">
                        <img src="/img/request-creator.png" alt="URL to prove Verified Creator"/>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-block feature-left">
                    <div class="feature-text">
                        <div class="feature-step">
                            <div class="feature-number">3</div>
                            <p>Within 24-48 hours you will receive your Verified Creator badge!</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-block feature-left">
                    <div class="feature-text">
                        <div class="feature-step">
                            <div class="feature-number">4</div>
                            <p>Now you can include that badge in any stickers you create with that alias.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-image">
                        <img src="/img/creator-screenshot.png" alt="Verified Creator Badge in sticker"/>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
    <section class="content-section">
        <div class="content-container">
            <header class="section-header">
                <h2 id="sign-video">To sign a video</h2>
                <p class="section-intro">Follow these steps to add a verifiable sticker to your video.</p>
            </header>
            <ol class="steps-grid to-sign-video">
                <li class="step">
                    <h3 class="step-title">1. Create the video</h3>
                    <p class="step-text">Create your video that you want to sign.</p>
                    <div class="feature-image step-media">
                        <img src="/img/cut.jpg" alt="Verified Creator Badge in sticker"/>
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li class="step">
                    <h3 class="step-title">2. Create a message sticker</h3>
                    <p class="step-text">
                        Make a sticker with a message that clearly describes the video and its key content.
                    </p>
                    <div class="feature-image step-media">
                        <img src="/img/creator-screenshot-message.png" alt="Verified Creator Badge in sticker"/>
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li class="step">
                    <h3 class="step-title">3. Create a QR code sticker</h3>
                    <p class="step-text">
                        Generate a QR code sticker that encodes the message and includes your Verified Creator badge.
                    </p>
                    <figure class="step-media">
                        <img src="/img/sample-qr.png" alt="Example of a QR code sticker with a Verified Creator badge" loading="lazy"/>
                    </figure>
                </li>
                <li class="step">
                    <h3 class="step-title">4. Edit the sticker into your video</h3>
                    <p class="step-text">
                        Place the sticker so it’s ~<strong>10%</strong>
                        of the video’s width (in pixels). Show it in the first few seconds so viewers immediately know the video is signed.
                    </p>
                    <figure class="step-media">
                        <img
                            src="/img/video-sticker.png"
                            alt="Sticker placed in the corner of a video during the first few seconds"
                            loading="lazy"/>
                    </figure>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </div>
    </section>
    <section class="content-panel panel-light-grey">
        <div class="content-container">
            <header class="section-header">
                <h2 id="scan-sticker">Scan the sticker</h2>
            </header>
            <ol class="steps">
                <li class="step mb-2">
                    <h3 class="step-title">1. Scan from a computer screen</h3>
                    <p class="step-text">
                        Point your phone camera at the video playing on your computer. The not.bot app will automatically open and show the
                        signature.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li class="step">
                    <h3 class="step-title">2. Scan from your phone</h3>
                    <p class="step-text">
                        Take a screen capture (press Volume Up + Power), then open the screenshot in the not.bot app. The app will scan the
                        sticker.
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ol>
            <div class="emphasis-block verified-creator">
                <div class="emphasis-content">
                    <header class="section-header">
                        <h2 class="dark-cyan">Internet-Wide Recognition</h2>
                    </header>
                    <div>
                        <strong>
                        Everywhere you use that alias, regardless of platform, or even in person, you can include your Verified Creator badge so
                        everyone knows it’s you.
                        </strong>
                    </div>
                    <ul class="common-list mt-1">
                        <li>A YouTube creator that wants to engage with fans on X or Discord can use a Verified Creator sticker so everyone
                            knows it is really them.</li>
                        <li>A TikTok creator that posts longer content on YouTube can use a sticker to prove the YouTube account isn’t just a
                            deepfake.</li>
                        <li>Reporters can use stickers to label the videos they take</li>
                        <li>Content creators can prove their online identity at in-person events like conferences.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <div class="mt-2">
                        <strong>What stops people from copy-pasting my not.bot sticker on their deepfaked video?</strong>
                    </div>
                    <ul class="common-list mt-1">
                        <li>Nothing.  But if the message in the not.bot sticker is clear and complete, then anyone that scans it will know it is obviously wrong for the video it’s on.</li>
                        </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
{% endblock %}
{% block scripts %}
    <script>
        // Expandable section functionality
        const autonomousToggle = document.getElementById('autonomousToggle');
        const autonomousContent = document.getElementById('autonomousContent');
        const chevron = autonomousToggle.querySelector('.expand-chevron');
        autonomousToggle.addEventListener('click', function () {
            autonomousContent.classList.toggle('active');
            chevron.classList.toggle('rotated');
        });
        console.log('not.bot Reserved Names page loaded');
    </script>
{% endblock %}